[{"id":33753,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Complex Number","question":"","options":["$\\frac{17}{2}$","8","9","$\\frac{15}{2}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$|z - 2| \\leq 4 \\Rightarrow (x - 2)^2 + y^2 \\leq 16$<br>$|z - 2| + |z + 2| = 5 \\Rightarrow \\dfrac{x^2}{a^2} + \\dfrac{y^2}{b^2} = 1$<br>$\\Rightarrow \\dfrac{4x^2}{25} + \\dfrac{4y^2}{9} = 1$<br><br>Maximum value of $|z_1 - z_2| = 6 + \\dfrac{5}{2} = \\dfrac{17}{2}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (28 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":33791,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Complex Number","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>i</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≤</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>Putting, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>y</mi></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>≤</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mi>i</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>For the circle represented in equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>i</mi></mfenced></math>, centre is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> and radius, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p><p>It is given that, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><menclose notation=\"top\"><mi>z</mi></menclose><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>i</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≤</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>i</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≤</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>≤</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>≤</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>So, the line passing through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> and perpendicular to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> is given by, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6a48608a-82e8-4389-92ee-b95c00c27545.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 272px;\"/></p><p>So, the distance of line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> from the centre <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> is given by,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p><p>Now, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> can be rewritten as,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo> </mo><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi><mo> </mo><mtext>or</mtext><mo> </mo><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></math></p><p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>≡</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mo>≡</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>31</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>31</mn><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mi>β</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>β</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>36</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (01 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":33809,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Complex Number","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Put&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp;in the given expression and equate the imaginary part to zero.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>i</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>i</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>i</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>But&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Im</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>i</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>i</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>11</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>11</mn><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>16</mn><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>24</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>30</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>45</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>24</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>16</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>11</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>11</mn><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>26</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>61</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>11</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>11</mn><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>26</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>61</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8757;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>&#8800;</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>So, put&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>13</mn><mn>11</mn></mfrac></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#945;</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>11</mn><msup><mi>&#945;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mfrac><msup><mn>13</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mn>11</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>26</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mfrac><mn>13</mn><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>61</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>121</mn><msup><mi>&#945;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>840</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>242</mn><msup><mi>&#945;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1680</mn></math></p><p>Hence this is the required answer.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (11 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":33945,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Complex Number","question":"","options":["either on the real axis or on a circle passing through the origin","on a circle with centre at the origin","either on the real axis or on a circle not passing through the origin","on the imaginary axis"],"answer":0,"solution":"Let $z=x+$ iy $(\\because x \\neq 1$ as $z \\neq 1)$\n$z^2=\\left(x^2-y^2\\right)+i(2 x y)$\n$\\frac{z^2}{z-1}$ is real \n$\\Rightarrow$ its imaginary part $=0$\n$\\Rightarrow 2 x y(x-1)-y\\left(x^2-y^2\\right)=0$\n$\\Rightarrow y\\left(x^2+y^2-2 x\\right)=0$\n$\\Rightarrow y=0 ; x^2+y^2-2 x=0$\n$\\therefore \\mathrm{z}$ lies either on real axis or on a circle through origin.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (Offline)","image":null},{"id":33869,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Complex Number","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Let</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>i</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>i</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><m